e NIST statistical tests to be passed: one based on\ntwo-hybrid mixed chaotic logistic maps and one based on two-hybrid mixed\nchaotic Henon maps, where each chaotic algorithm runs side-by-side and starts\nwith random initial conditions and parameters (encryption keys). The resulting\nhybrid PRNGs passed many of the NIST statistical test suits.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 4 Dec 2020 21:52:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-08"}
